  <prompt>
    Build `<BodyEditor />` at `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/BodyEditor.tsx`. Supports two modes via `bodyFormat: 'html' | 'plaintext'` prop with an explicit user-facing toggle.

    Requirements (FR-06):
    - `bodyFormat='html'`: lightweight rich-text editor. Bare minimum toolbar: Bold, Italic, Underline, Bulleted list, Numbered list, Link. Output: clean HTML (no inline styles beyond what the toolbar produces; no `<font>` tags; no `<script>` / `<iframe>`).
    - `bodyFormat='plaintext'`: monospace `<Textarea />` from Fluent v9. Output: plain text, no HTML tags.
    - Toggle: explicit user control labeled "Format: HTML / Plain text" rendered as a Fluent `<RadioGroup />` or `<Switch />`. Toggling from HTML â†’ PlainText strips HTML tags (best-effort, may lose markup). Toggling PlainText â†’ HTML wraps text in `<p>` tags (best-effort).
    - Component is CONTROLLED: receives `value: string`, `bodyFormat: 'html' | 'plaintext'`, `onChange(value: string, bodyFormat)` from engine reducer.
    - Keyboard accessible: focus visible, Tab moves into editor, Esc moves focus to toggle.
    - For the HTML editor implementation: use an existing minimal library OR roll a simple `contentEditable` div with sanitization. DO NOT pull in a heavy editor like TipTap, Lexical, or Quill â€” those add ~150 KB to the bundle (NFR-08 perf).

    Files:
    - `subcomponents/BodyEditor.tsx` (NEW)
    - Update `EmailComposer/index.ts` to export `BodyEditor`
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend dev with Fluent UI v9 + light-rich-editor experience. Familiar with `contentEditable` quirks + HTML sanitization basics.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `<BodyEditor />` compiles, lint-clean. Switching to HTML mode shows the toolbar + editable region; switching to PlainText shows a monospace Textarea. Toggle preserves content best-effort. No heavy editor library added. Bundle size delta < 20 KB.
  </goal>

  <context>
